The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised clustering using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves using domain-specific transformations, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The use of Graph-based Activity Regularization (GAR) terms also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Auto-clustering Output Layer (ACOL), which is a neural network architecture, indicating neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with clustering tasks on image datasets, which suggests natural language processing (cs.CL) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
